document: This dataset contains records of Medical Science Liaison (MSL) engagement activities with Healthcare Professionals (HCPs) and Healthcare Organizations (HCOs), including call details, participant information, and location data.

metadata.identifier: MSL Engagement Activity with HCP and HCO.xlsx

columns.description: Unique identifier for each MSL engagement call.
Date and time of the MSL engagement call.
Status of the MSL engagement call (e.g., Planned, Submitted, Cancelled).
Date and time when the call record was loaded into the system.
Last day of the month the call took place.
Last day of the week the call took place.
Indicates if the call was a face-to-face meeting.
Indicates if the call was a virtual meeting.
Indicates if the call involved digital promotion.
Indicates if the call was of another type.
Indicates if the call was a group call.
Number of attendees in the call.
Indicates if the call was for staff only.
Name of the product discussed in the call.
Source of the call data (e.g., Salesforce, CRM, Veeva).
Categorization of the call (e.g., Core, Others).
Description of the call based on a code (e.g., LTC, Retail, HOSP).
Flag indicating PDRP (likely a specific program or initiative).
Flag indicating AMA (likely a specific program or initiative) contact.
Name of the customer (HCP or HCO representative).
DEA (Drug Enforcement Administration) number of the customer (if applicable).
NPI (National Provider Identifier) number of the customer (if applicable).
Professional designation of the customer (e.g., DMD, UNK, PA).
Type of customer (HCO: Healthcare Organization, HCP: Healthcare Professional).
Unique identifier for the customer's location or account.
Flag indicating if the HCP is a target customer.
Tier of the HCP target customer.
Flag indicating if the HCO is a target customer.
Identifier for the parent HCO (if applicable).
Name of the parent HCO (if applicable).
Type of the parent HCO (if applicable).
Address from MDM (Master Data Management) system.
City from MDM (Master Data Management) system.
State from MDM (Master Data Management) system.
Zip code from MDM (Master Data Management) system.
Identifier from MDM (Master Data Management) system.

document: This dataset contains prescription transaction data, including customer information, prescription details, and pricing information.

columns.description: Unique identifier for the medical provider.
Type of customer (e.g., Healthcare Organization, Specialty Distributor, Healthcare Provider).
Address of the customer from MDM Golden database.
City of the customer from MDM Golden database.
State of the customer from MDM Golden database.
Zip code of the customer from MDM Golden database.
Professional designation of the prescriber (e.g., Nurse Practitioner, Physician Assistant).
National Provider Identifier (NPI) of the prescriber.
Flag indicating if the prescriber is an AMA contact (1=Yes, 0=No).
Flag indicating if the prescriber is part of a PDRP program (1=Yes, 0=No).
Type of prescription (e.g., Retail, Specialty Pharmacy).
National Drug Code (NDC) of the medication.
Wholesale Acquisition Cost (WAC) price of the medication.
Flag indicating inclusion in a specific program (Y=Yes, N=No).
Flag indicating if a voucher was provided (Y=Yes, N=No).
Type of prescription fill (New or Refill).
Type of payment from the primary payer.
Name of the primary payer's Pharmacy Benefit Manager (PBM).
Number of days the medication supply is intended to last.
